%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEnergy-efficient%20units%20are%20better%20for%20the%20environment%20and%20keep%20your%20cooling%20costs%20low.%20Most%20window%20AC%20picks%20in%20our%20best%20air%20conditioner%20guide%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energystar.gov%2Fabout%2Fhow-energy-star-works%2Fenergy-star-certification%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnergy%20Star%3C%2Fa%3E%20certified%2C%20but%20no%20portable%20units%20have%20earned%20this%20designation.%20We've%20found%20that%20window%20units%20with%20a%20variable%20speed%20compressor%20are%20the%20most%20efficient%20at%20cooling%20and%20the%20cheapest%20to%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBtu%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20common%20for%20model%20numbers%20for%20the%20same%20units%20to%20vary%20by%20one%20or%20two%20digits%3B%20this%20usually%20denotes%20different%20Btu%20ratings%20%E2%80%94%20a%20measurement%20of%20the%20cooling%20power%20of%20your%20air%20conditioner.%20It%20may%20be%20tempting%20to%20buy%20an%20AC%20with%2C%20but%20if%20you%20get%20a%20unit%20that%20is%20too%20big%20for%20your%20room%2C%20it%20will%20cool%20too%20quickly%20without%20removing%20the%20moisture%2C%20leaving%20a%20cold%2C%20clammy%20environment.%20Use%20the%20table%20below%20(from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energystar.gov%2Fproductfinder%2Fproduct%2Fcertified-room-air-conditioners%2Fresults%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnergy%20Star%20website%3C%2Fa%3E)%20to%20determine%20what%20Btu%20your%20room%20requires%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ctable%3E%3Ccolgroup%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3C%2Fcolgroup%3E%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3ERoom%20size%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3ECooling%20power%20needed%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E100%20to%20150%20square%20feet%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E5%2C000%20Btu%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%22