2%80%94short%20for%20Trump%20Always%20Chickens%20Out%E2%80%94will%20prevail.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20has%20backed%20down%20or%20pivoted%20from%20other%20announcements%20that%20shook%20markets%20this%20year%2C%20sparking%20big%20relief%20rallies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-today-trump-tariffs-sp500-japan-korea-trade-war-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStocks%20dropped%20on%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariff%20tough%20talk%20back%20in%20the%20spotlight.%20Now%2C%20investors%20are%20hoping%20it's%20TACO%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-taco-tariffs-buy-the-dip-trade-war-sp500-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETACO%20trade%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20term%20coined%20by%20Financial%20Times%20columnist%20Robert%20Armstrong%20that's%20short%20for%20Trump%20Always%20Chickens%20Out%20%E2%80%94%20is%20back%20in%20the%20market%20zeitgeist%20with%20Trump%20announcing%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20Japan%20and%20South%20Korea%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20on%20August%201%2C%20as%20well%20teasing%20steep%20tariffs%20on%20a%20handful%20of%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20dropped%20almost%201%25%20and%20the%20Dow%20lost%20more%20than%20400%20points%20on%20the%20news%20as%20investors%20fretted%20over%20the%20trade%20war%20again%20after%20weeks%20of%20positive%20developments%2C%20including%20progress%20with%20key%20trading%20partners%20like%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TACO%20acronym%20caught%20on%20with%20investors%20because%20of%20how%20frequently%20Trump%20has%20backed%20down%20or%20pivoted%20from%20policies%20that%20roiled%20markets%20(see%20the%20April%202%20to%20April%209%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-today-ai-meta-microsoft-earnings-ai-stocks-nvidia-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELiberation%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20pivot%20or%20his%20backing%20down%20from%20threats%20to%20fire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-backs-off-firing-jerome-powell-markets-rally-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Trump%20has%20backed%20down%2C%20investors%20have%20piled%20into%20stocks.%20The%20market's%20increasingly%20sanguine%20attitude%20about%20Trump's%20trade%20war%20pushed%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20back%20to%20all-time%20highs%20after%20a%20near-20%25%20drop%20from%20February%20to%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20investors%20are%20waiting%20to%20see%20if%20Trump%20walks%20back%20his%20latest%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Tom%20Essaye%2C%20founder%20of%20Sevens%20Report%20Research%2C%20who%20has%20clients%20including%20advisors%20at%20UBS%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%2C%20JPMorgan%2C%20and%20more%2C%20Trump%20will%20likely%20ease%20his%20latest%20aggressive%20tariff%20talk%20again.%20And%20if%20he%20doesn't%20initially%2C%20investors%20feel%20confident%20that%20he%20will%20eventually%2C%20Essaye%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20on%20Monday%20was%20pronounced%20relative%20to%20the%20staid%20moves%20in%20stocks%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20but%20they%20were%20nothing%20compared%20to%20the%20plunge%20that%20rocked%20the%20market%20in%20April.%20For%20the%20most%20part%2C%20investors%20have%20stopped%20reacting%20so%20intensely%20to%20trade%20updates%2C%20preferring%20to%20focus%20on%20things%20more%20immediately%20relevant%20to%20stock%20prices%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-stocks-have-rallied-furiously-since-their-liberation-day-losses-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elike%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegardless%20of%20what%20sort%20of%20shocking%20headline%20or%20confusing%20headline%20comes%20out%20of%20the%20administration%2C%20the%20administration%20will%20not%20purposefully%20do%20something%20that%20really%20hurts%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Essaye%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20can%20come%20out%20tomorrow%20and%20say%20that%20all%20of%20the%20reciprocal%20tariff%20rates%20are%20in%20force%20for%20the%20forseeable%20future%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20the%20market%20would%20go%20down%20all%20that%20much%20because%20the%20market%20would%20not%20believe%20for%20one%20minute%20that%20it%20was%20going%20to%20last%20very%20long%2C%20and%20defnitely%20not%20long%20enough%20to%20hurt%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Essaye%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20medium-term%2C%20however%2C%20Trump%20risks%20hurting%20economic%20growth%20and%20profits%20due%20to%20the%20uncertainty%20he's%20creating%20for%20business%20owners%2C%20Essaye%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20making%20capital%20allocation%20decisions%20around%20Trump's%20trade%20rhetoric%20is%20different%20than%20a%20business%20owner%20making%20planning%20decisions%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20idea%20that%20the%20administration%20will%20not%20purposefully%20do%20anything%20they%20think%20will%20hurt%20the%20economy%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20their%20policies%20won't%20ultimately%20hurt%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20whole%20pile%20of%20history%20that%20says%20that%20the%20things%20they%20are%20doing%20do%20not%20turn%20out%20well%20for%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20they%20are%20sort%20of%20flying%20in%20the%20face%20of%20that%2C%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20see%20what%20happens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaco-trade-trump-tariffs-investors-stock-market-japan-south-korea-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751966101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686c1b823d5881a51c1cd077%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.b